# Config Rules

## Config Files (config/)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `site.ts` | Site name, contact, social URLs, booking options, newsletter, feature flags. Export `siteConfig` and `SiteConfig` type. |
| `colors.ts` | `aestheticsColors` — primary, secondary, accent, gradients. Used in components and email. |
| `typography.ts` | `typography`, `layout`, `textColors` — responsive heading/body classes and container padding. Use in all pages/sections. |
| `design-system.ts` | Additional design tokens if needed. |
| `badge-styles.ts` | `badgeBackgroundClass` — shared class for section badges (e.g. "Popular Treatments"). |
| `fonts.ts` | Font loading notes (Montserrat via CSS). |

## Site Config (config/site.ts)

- Contact: `siteConfig.contact.phone`, `siteConfig.contact.email`, `siteConfig.contact.address`
- Social: `siteConfig.social.instagram`, `.facebook`, `.youtube`, `.tiktok`
- Newsletter: `siteConfig.newsletter.welcomeDiscountPercent`, `discountCodePrefix`, `discountValidDays`
- Booking: `siteConfig.booking.*` (minAdvanceBooking, bufferTime, etc.)
- Features: `siteConfig.features.blog`, `.reviews`, `.onlinePayments`, etc.
- Use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for overrides; provide defaults for all keys.

## Adding New Config

1. Add key to appropriate file in `config/`
2. Export type if needed (e.g. `SiteConfig` in site.ts)
3. Use in components via `import { siteConfig } from "@/config/site"` (or typography, colors, etc.)

## Environment Variables

- Public: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_PHONE_NUMBER`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_BUSINESS_EMAIL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCIAL_*`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_ADDRESS_*`
- Server-only: `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `SENDGRID_*`, `ADMIN_EMAIL`
- Never commit secrets; document new vars in `.env.example` or README if needed.
